{
  "doc_id": "32970",
  "text": "Content analysis involves a systematic, quantitative analysis of content, usually texts, images, or other symbolic matter [CITATION_1] . According to [CITATION_2] , ''content analysis seeks to demonstrate the meaning of written or visual sources by systematically allocating their content to predetermined, detailed categories, and then both quantifying and interpreting the outcomes'' (p. 51). As a methodology, content analysis allows researchers to determine the presence, meanings, and relationships of certain words or concepts within the text. We used content analysis to systematically analyze the coverage of men's and women's sport in televised news media.",
